Usefull Links:-

Cilium installation: https://docs.cilium.io/en/stable/gettingstarted/k8s-install-default/
CIDR Calculator: https://iamroot.tech/cidr/
Useful commands: https://gitlab.com/nanuchi/k8s-administrator-course/-/blob/master/02.%20Install%20Cluster/commands.md


1) Install pod network plugin by using below code on Master Node

CILIUM_CLI_VERSION=$(curl -s https://raw.githubusercontent.com/cilium/cilium-cli/main/stable.txt)
CLI_ARCH=amd64
if [ "$(uname -m)" = "aarch64" ]; then CLI_ARCH=arm64; fi
curl -L --fail --remote-name-all https://github.com/cilium/cilium-cli/releases/download/${CILIUM_CLI_VERSION}/cilium-linux-${CLI_ARCH}.tar.gz{,.sha256sum}
sha256sum --check cilium-linux-${CLI_ARCH}.tar.gz.sha256sum
sudo tar xzvfC cilium-linux-${CLI_ARCH}.tar.gz /usr/local/bin
rm cilium-linux-${CLI_ARCH}.tar.gz{,.sha256sum}

Note:

To install different IP address range use below command

cilium install --set ipam.operator.clutserPoolIP4PodCIDRList="10.1.0.0/9"

2) Install "CILIUM"

cilium install 

3) check cilium status by using below commands

cilium status
kubectl -n kube-system exec cilium-2hq5z -- cilium-dbg status
cilium connectivity test

4) Check nodes

kubectl get node

5) check pods under kube-system namespace

kubectl get pods -n kube-system

6) check pod ip address of cilium

kubectl get pods -o wide -n kube-system

